armips
------------------------------------------
Assembler for various ARM and MIPS platforms

Runtime requirements:
  cygwin-3.6.7-1
  libgcc1-13.4.0-1
  libintl8-0.22.5-1
  libstdc++6-13.4.0-1

Build requirements:
(besides corresponding -devel packages)
  binutils-2.46-1
  cmake-4.2.1-1
  cygport-0.37.7-1
  gcc-core-13.4.0-1
  gcc-g++-13.4.0-1
  ninja-1.13.2-1

Canonical website:
  https://github.com/Kingcom/armips

Canonical download:
  https://github.com/Kingcom/armips/archive/refs/tags/v0.11.0.tar.gz

-------------------------------------------

Build instructions:
  1. unpack armips-0.11.0-X-src.tar.xz
  2. if you use setup to install this src package,
     it will be unpacked under /usr/src automatically
        % cd /usr/src
        % cygport ./armips-0.11.0-X.cygport all

This will create:
  /usr/src/armips-0.11.0-X-src.tar.xz
  /usr/src/armips-0.11.0-X.tar.xz

-------------------------------------------

Files included in the binary package:

(armips)
  /usr/bin/armips.exe
  /usr/share/doc/Cygwin/armips.README
  /usr/share/doc/armips/LICENSE.txt
  /usr/share/doc/armips/Readme.md

------------------

